<HEADLINE>
FT  08 NOV 94 / Economic Watch: Trade gap grows in Spain
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Spain's January-September accumulated trade deficit widened by 5.1 per cent
to Pta1,860bn (Pounds 9.1bn) against the first nine months of 1993 despite a
continuing strong performance by the export sector, which grew by 33 per
cent over the period. The volume of imports and exports is expected to
increase during the fourth quarter of the year, although year-on-year growth
rates will be more moderate because trade already began to increase strongly
in the final three months of 1993. The finance ministry said import growth
showed that domestic demand was expanding at a higher rate than forecast.
Tom Burns, Madrid
Greece had a Dollars 23m (Pounds 14m) current account surplus in July,
against a July 1993 surplus of Dollars 1.152bn. The January-July current
account deficit was Dollars 1.071bn, sharply off a Dollars 205m surplus in
the same seven-month 1993 period.
Austrian unemployment in October was steady from September at 4.4 per cent
of the workforce, but was up from 4.2 per cent in October last year.
</TEXT>
