FT  07 NOV 94 / UK Company News: London United in Pounds 23m buy-out
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GRAHAM BOWLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
London United, the west London bus company, has been bought by its staff in
a Pounds 22.9m deal, backed by Montagu Private Equity and 3i, the investment
capital group.
It becomes the ninth London bus company to be sold by London Regional
Transport this year and almost completes LRT's privatisation programme which
so far has raised more than Pounds 211m.
London United, operates 450 buses in south-west London, as well as the
Heathrow to central London Airbus. It employs 1,450 staff and had Pounds
36.6m turnover in the year to March 1994.
