<TEXT>
Sir, May I draw your attention to another problem with the newly-introduced
airport tax ('Airlines hit at levy on departures', October 31).
In addition to the confusion over European rates there is the problem of
double levying where passengers wish to make use of the fact that London has
five airports. Rates for London-Geneva-London are Pounds 5 when travelling
in and out of the same airport, but Pounds 10 when flying from Heathrow and
returning to Gatwick, or any other combination.
Where is the logic in this?
Duncan J McKay,
