<HEADLINE>
FT  07 NOV 94 / Business Travel: Give and take
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Even the bedside Gideon Bible is not safe from the clutches of business
executives staying in hotels, says a survey by Britain's Reed Travel Group.
Coat-hangers, cutlery and TV remote-controls are other items they take,
while nightclothes, underwear and ties top the list of things they leave.
Younger business travellers are the most light-fingered. British executives
visit the US on business more than their European counterparts. One in five
business travellers takes exercise while away. The survey covered 1,270
business travellers.
