<HEADLINE>
FT  07 NOV 94 / Accountants face skills demand
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Employers are demanding more skills when looking for accountants and are
more likely to take on temporary staff, Robert Half, the recruitment
consultant, has found.
A survey, based on interviews with 200 senior managers, found that only one
in five now predicted that they would take on extra permanent staff compared
with more than one in four six months ago.
